1. *Stric* je juče došao u posetu. (Uncle came to visit yesterday.)
2. Imam *strica* u Americi. (I have an uncle in America.)
3. *Stricu*, da li želiš da popijemo kafu zajedno? (Uncle, do you want to have coffee together?)
4. Upoznao sam *strica* mog prijatelja i jako mi se dopao. (I met my friend's uncle and I liked him a lot.)
5. Sinoć sam razgovarao sa svojim *stricom* o budućnosti. (Last night I talked to my uncle about the future.)
6. *Strica* me je naučio da vozim bicikl. (My uncle taught me how to ride a bike.)
7. *Stric* će nas prevesti do aerodroma sutra. (Uncle will drive us to the airport tomorrow.)
8. Moja sestra i njen *stric* su veoma bliski. (My sister and her uncle are very close.)
9. Moja porodica se sastoji od majke, oca, sestre i *strica*. (My family consists of mother, father, sister and uncle.)
10. *Stric* je bio veoma ljut kada sam mu rekao da sam pao na ispitu. (Uncle was very angry when I told him I failed the exam.)

Note: In Serbian language, the word "stric" means "uncle". The different forms of the word "stric" used in the above sentences are: "stric" (nominative case, subject), "strica" (accusative case, direct object), "stricu" (vocative case, when addressing someone), "stricom" (instrumental case, when indicating a tool or means), and "stric" (genitive case, when indicating possession).